data.text: I used to eat here all the time I haven't been here in several months what a disappointment I do not recommend it to sushi is paper thin that you not make half rolls no more they used to all the time for the several years I came here please don't waste your money

data.title: Best all you can eat sushi!
data.text: Definitely our only favorite sushi spot here in Lancaster. My 7 year old daughter LOVES their baked mussels and my husband and I are I love with their spider hand rolls. We brought my sister in law, and she happens to be very picky with sushi and she loved the place! This place is a must try!!!!

data.title: Great Japanese food in Lancaster Ca
data.text: A great little restaurant for reasonable price Japanese food.  Bento Specials start at $9.00 to $12.00.  A lot of foods for the price they charged.  They also often all you can eat sushi special for lunch run around $19.95 per person and dinner for $24.99 per person.  Large Kirin Ichiban cost $5.95 and a small hot sake cost $3.50.  Soda or ice tea cost $1.75.  Service is excellent here.  A great place to eat sushi and not costing a lot of money.

data.title: Good sushi but not busy enought to always be fresh
data.text: My family and I enjoy sushi, and have tried Miso, a few times, this time happened to be a mid week visit and we found that the sushi was kind of fishy  It was good but for those of you that are like my wife) & don't like that fishy smell that comes with some sushi that is a day old or so you will be disappointed.
